{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:job.23",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 23,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 23",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 23 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.23.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.23.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:2",
      "text": "Yea, I know that pleading is out of my reach; and his hand has been made heavy upon my groaning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.23.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:3",
      "text": "Who would then know that I might find him, and come to an end of the matter?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.23.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:4",
      "text": "And I would plead my own cause, and he would fill my mouth with arguments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.23.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:5",
      "text": "And I would know the remedies which he would speak to me, and I would perceive what he would tell me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.23.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:6",
      "text": "Though he should come on me in his great strength, then he would not threaten me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.23.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:7",
      "text": "for truth and reproof are from him; and he would bring forth my judgement to an end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.23.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:8",
      "text": "For if I shall go first, and exist no longer, still what do I know concerning the latter end?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.23.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:9",
      "text": "When he wrought on the left hand, then I observed it not: his right hand shall encompass me but I shall not see it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.23.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:10",
      "text": "For he knows already my way; and he has tried me as gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.23.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:11",
      "text": "And I will go forth according to his commandments, for I have kept his ways; and I shall not turn aside from his commandments,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.23.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:12",
      "text": "neither shall I transgress; but I have hid his words in my bosom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.23.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:13",
      "text": "And if too he has thus judged, who is he that has contradicted, for he has both willed a thing and done it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.23.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:14",
      "text": "Therefore am I troubled at him; and when I was reproved, I thought of him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.23.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:15",
      "text": "Therefore let me take good heed before him: I will consider, and be afraid of him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.23.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:16",
      "text": "But the Lord has softened my heart, and the Almighty has troubled me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.23.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:17",
      "text": "For I knew not that darkness would come upon me, and thick darkness has covered me before my face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
